text:
Hellooo HN, long time reader, first time poster.

I'm a final year cs undergrad student and this winter break I wanted to make my first real sort of end-to-end software. So I made wyd.chat.

It's a imessage analyzer kind thing - just looks at your texts to see who you text the most, when you text them, what you talk about, how many group chats you're in with them, etc etc.

I made it for fun but realized that the data kind of shows who I should prioritize in my life vs who I am not giving enough of my attention to. Just super interesting data.

Basic analytics is for free and full is for $6 one time. All data is stored locally and I truly have access to nothing.

I'm a super baby engineer so any feedback you might have I would be so grateful.

Happy new year!
